i.b: Re: 3000 Clearview Way Traffic Study Update

page.text: Hexagon Transportation Consultant, Inc. has completed this update to the 2012 Traffic Impact
Study for the proposed San Mateo Executive Office Park Development located at 3000 Clearview
Way in San Mateo. It is our understanding that the applicant now wishes to add a parking garage
to the project. This would be to accommodate cars that are now parking off site at a leased lot.
However, the size of the project has not changed, and the net increase in office space remains
98,740 square feet. Because there is no change to the proposed office space, there would be no
increase/change in trip generation compared to the trips analyzed in the 2012 traffic study.
The purpose of this study is to confirm that existing traffic conditions have not changed since the
The previous 2012 traffic study included 4 intersections and 6 freeway segments. The intersection
analysis was based on traffic counts collected in December 2011, and the freeway segment
analysis was based on the 2011 Congestion Management Program (CMP) Annual Monitoring
New turning movement counts were collected at the study intersections. Bicycle and pedestrian
counts were also collected at all the study intersections.
The most current 2013 San Mateo County CMP monitoring report was used for the freeway
segment analysis. Existing 2014 levels of service at the 4 study intersections and 6 freeway
segments were calculated and compared to that of the 2012 traffic study. The following paragraphs
present the results of the analysis.

text.b: Existing Intersection Levels of Service Analysis

page.text: The results of the level of service analysis under the 2014 existing conditions are summarized in
Table 1 below. For comparison purposes, the results of the 2012 existing conditions are also
included in the table. The results show that the levels of service for the four signalized
intersections under 2014 existing conditions are comparable to those of the 2012 existing
conditions. All signalized intersections operate at LOS B or better under 2014 existing conditions,
which is within the City’s adopted level of service standard. The level of service calculation sheets

text.b: Existing Freeway Levels of Service Analysis

page.text: The existing levels of service for the study freeway segment on SR 92 between I-280 and US 101
were obtained from Table 3 of the 2013 CMP Annual Monitoring Report. The results show that the
freeway segments currently operate at an unacceptable LOS F for the AM peak and LOS E for the
PM peak, which are comparable to results from the 2011 CMP report.
As there is no change to the proposed office space, there would be no increase in trips on the
freeway compared to the trips analyzed in the 2012 traffic study report. The project impact to the
Route 92 freeway was found to be less than significant.
New traffic counts were conducted to determine 2014 existing conditions. The results show that
